h2. 2. Ghostty Terminal

Ghostty is a fast, GPU-accelerated terminal emulator with native platform integration. It pairs well with tmux for a persistent session workflow.

h3. Installation

Ghostty does not ship in most Linux package managers. Download the official binary or {{.deb}} package from the official site:

[Ghostty Install Docs|https://ghostty.org/docs/install/binary]

For Debian/Ubuntu, download the {{.deb}} and install:

{code:language=bash}
sudo dpkg -i ghostty_*.deb
{code}

h3. Configuration

Ghostty reads config from {{~/.config/ghostty/config}}.

{code:language=none}
# ~/.config/ghostty/config

# Auto-start tmux on launch, creating or attaching to a session named "main"
command = "tmux new-session -A -s main -c ~ 'fish --login --interactive'"

# Adaptive theme: dark mode uses Catppuccin Frappe, light mode uses Catppuccin Latte
theme = dark:catppuccin-frappe,light:catppuccin-latte
{code}

{note}
Replace {{fish}} and {{tmux}} in the {{command}} value with the full paths from {{which fish}} and {{which tmux}} if Ghostty cannot resolve them from your {{PATH}} at launch time.
{note}

