h2. 3. tmux

tmux is a terminal multiplexer that lets you run multiple terminal sessions within a single window, keep sessions alive after disconnecting, and split panes for multitasking.

h3. Installation

*Ubuntu/Debian:*
{code:language=bash}
sudo apt install tmux
{code}

*Arch Linux:*
{code:language=bash}
sudo pacman -S tmux
{code}

*Fedora:*
{code:language=bash}
sudo dnf install tmux
{code}

h3. Configuration

tmux reads config from {{~/.config/tmux/tmux.conf}}. Create the directory and file:

{code:language=bash}
mkdir -p ~/.config/tmux
{code}

{code:language=none}
# ~/.config/tmux/tmux.conf

# Default shell
set-option -g default-shell /usr/bin/fish
set -g default-command "/usr/bin/fish -l"

# Terminal color support
set -g default-terminal "screen-256color"

# Mouse support
set -g mouse on

# Change prefix from Ctrl-b to Ctrl-Space
unbind C-b
set -g prefix C-Space
bind C-Space send-prefix

# Vi-style key bindings in copy mode
setw -g mode-keys vi

# Pane resizing with prefix + hjkl
bind -r h resize-pane -L 5
bind -r j resize-pane -D 5
bind -r k resize-pane -U 5
bind -r l resize-pane -R 5

# Intuitive split bindings
bind | split-window -h
bind - split-window -v
unbind '"'
unbind %

# 1-based window and pane indexing
set -g base-index 1
setw -g pane-base-index 1

# Status bar styling
set -g status-bg colour235
set -g status-fg white
set -g status-interval 5
set -g status-left-length 40
set -g status-right-length 100
set -g status-left '#[fg=green]#S'
set -g status-right '#[fg=yellow]%Y-%m-%d #[fg=cyan]%H:%M'
set-window-option -g window-status-current-style fg=black,bg=green

# Plugins
set -g @plugin 'tmux-plugins/tpm'
set -g @plugin 'tmux-plugins/tmux-sensible'
set -g @plugin 'tmux-plugins/tmux-resurrect'
set -g @plugin 'tmux-plugins/tmux-continuum'
set -g @plugin 'tmux-plugins/tmux-prefix-highlight'
set -g @plugin 'tmux-plugins/tmux-yank'

run '~/.tmux/plugins/tpm/tpm'
{code}

{note}
Update the {{default-shell}} and {{default-command}} paths to match the output of {{which fish}} on your system. On some distros, Fish may live at {{/usr/local/bin/fish}} rather than {{/usr/bin/fish}}.
{note}

h3. Plugin Manager (TPM)

Install [tmux Plugin Manager (TPM)|https://github.com/tmux-plugins/tpm]:

{code:language=bash}
git clone https://github.com/tmux-plugins/tpm ~/.tmux/plugins/tpm
{code}

Then start tmux and install the plugins:

{code:language=bash}
tmux
# Inside tmux, press:
# Ctrl-Space + I   (capital I) to install plugins
{code}

h3. Linux-Specific: xclip for tmux-yank

The {{tmux-yank}} plugin requires {{xclip}} (or {{xsel}}) on Linux to interact with the system clipboard:

{code:language=bash}
sudo apt install xclip
{code}

{note}
On Wayland-based desktops, you may need {{wl-clipboard}} instead: {{sudo apt install wl-clipboard}}
{note}

h3. Useful tmux Key Bindings

||Key Binding||Action||
|{{Ctrl-Space}}|Prefix key|
|{{Ctrl-Space + \|}}|Split pane horizontally|
|{{Ctrl-Space + -}}|Split pane vertically|
|{{Ctrl-Space + h/j/k/l}}|Resize pane (repeatable)|
|{{Ctrl-Space + d}}|Detach from session|
|{{Ctrl-Space + I}}|Install plugins (TPM)|
|{{Ctrl-Space + [}}|Enter copy/scroll mode|
|{{q}}|Exit copy mode|

h3. Using tmux with Claude Code Agent Teams

Claude Code supports running agent teams — subagents that work in parallel on different parts of a task. tmux is the recommended environment for monitoring and managing these agent sessions.

*How it works:*

* Claude Code agent teams use tmux sessions to run background agents
* Each agent may create or attach to its own named tmux session
* You can observe an agent's live output by attaching to its session

*Key commands for working with agent sessions:*

{code:language=bash}
# List all active tmux sessions (agent sessions appear alongside your main session)
tmux ls

# Attach to an agent's session to observe its work
tmux attach -t <session-name>

# Detach from an agent session without killing it
# Press: Ctrl-Space + d
{code}

*Why this setup helps:*

* The named session approach ({{-s main}}) used in the Ghostty config means Claude Code can reliably attach and detach to known session names without ambiguity
* The {{tmux-resurrect}} and {{tmux-continuum}} plugins preserve agent sessions across terminal restarts, so long-running agents are not lost if you close your terminal
* Mouse support ({{set -g mouse on}}) lets you scroll through agent output without entering copy mode

{info}
For full Claude Code agent teams documentation, see: [Claude Code Agent Teams|https://code.claude.com/docs/en/agent-teams]
{info}

h3. Verify

{code:language=bash}
tmux -V
tmux ls
{code}

