h2. 5. Starship Prompt

[Starship|https://starship.rs/] is a minimal, fast, and highly customizable prompt for any shell. It works out of the box with sensible defaults.

h3. Installation

{code:language=bash}
curl -sS https://starship.rs/install.sh | sh
{code}

The installer places the {{starship}} binary at {{/usr/local/bin/starship}}.

h3. Configuration

No custom configuration is required to get a great-looking prompt. Starship uses its built-in defaults.

To enable Starship in Fish, add the following line to {{~/.config/fish/config.fish}}:

{code:language=bash}
starship init fish | source
{code}

This should already be present if you followed the Fish configuration section above.

h3. Verify

Open a new terminal (or run {{source ~/.config/fish/config.fish}}) and confirm the Starship prompt is active:

{code:language=bash}
starship --version
{code}

