h2. 6. Yazi File Manager

[Yazi|https://yazi-rs.github.io/] is a blazing fast terminal file manager written in Rust, with image previews, plugin support, and deep integration with tools like fzf, zoxide, and ripgrep.

h3. Dependencies

Install required system dependencies before installing Yazi:

{code:language=bash}
sudo apt install ffmpegthumbnailer p7zip-full jq poppler-utils fd-find ripgrep fzf zoxide imagemagick
{code}

Install {{glow}} for Markdown preview support. Download the appropriate binary from [Glow Releases|https://github.com/charmbracelet/glow/releases] and place it on your {{PATH}}:

{code:language=bash}
sudo mv glow /usr/local/bin/glow
chmod +x /usr/local/bin/glow
{code}

h3. Installation

*Arch Linux:*
{code:language=bash}
sudo pacman -S yazi
{code}

*All other distros — via Cargo (requires Rust):*
{code:language=bash}
# Install Rust if not already present
curl --proto '=https' --tlsv1.2 -sSf https://sh.rustup.rs | sh
source ~/.cargo/env

# Install Yazi
cargo install --locked yazi-fm yazi-cli
{code}

*Binary download (alternative):*

Download the pre-built binary from [Yazi GitHub Releases|https://github.com/sxyazi/yazi/releases] and move it to {{/usr/local/bin/}}.

h3. Configuration

Yazi reads config from {{~/.config/yazi/}}. Create the directory and the main config file:

{code:language=bash}
mkdir -p ~/.config/yazi
{code}

*~/.config/yazi/yazi.toml:*

{code:language=sql}
[mgr]
show_hidden = true
ratio = [1, 3, 5]

[[plugin.prepend_previewers]]
name = "*.md"
run = 'piper -- glow -s dark "$1"'
{code}

h3. Plugins

Install the official Yazi plugin collection:

{code:language=bash}
ya pack -a yazi-rs/plugins:bypass
ya pack -a yazi-rs/plugins:compress
ya pack -a yazi-rs/plugins:diff
ya pack -a yazi-rs/plugins:copy-file-contents
ya pack -a yazi-rs/plugins:what-size
ya pack -a yazi-rs/plugins:save-clipboard-to-file
{code}

h3. Shell Integration

The {{y}} wrapper function (defined in the Fish section above) handles changing your shell's working directory to wherever you navigate in Yazi. After setting it up, use {{y}} instead of {{yazi}} to launch the file manager.

h3. Verify

{code:language=bash}
yazi --version
y
{code}

