h2. 7. Volta (Node.js Version Manager)

[Volta|https://volta.sh/] is a hassle-free JavaScript toolchain manager. It lets you install and switch Node.js versions on a per-project basis, with no manual {{nvm use}} commands required.

h3. Installation

{code:language=bash}
curl https://get.volta.sh | bash
{code}

{note}
The Volta installer automatically modifies {{~/.bashrc}} and {{~/.profile}} for Bash users. Since we are using Fish shell, the automatic PATH setup will not apply. You must manually add Volta to your Fish config.
{note}

h3. Fish Shell Integration

Add the following to {{~/.config/fish/config.fish}} (this should already be present if you followed the Fish configuration section):

{code:language=bash}
set -gx VOLTA_HOME "$HOME/.volta"
fish_add_path "$VOLTA_HOME/bin"
{code}

Reload your Fish config:

{code:language=bash}
source ~/.config/fish/config.fish
{code}

h3. Install Node.js

{code:language=bash}
# Install the latest LTS version of Node.js (recommended for most projects)
volta install node
{code}

Volta automatically sets this as your default Node.js version. All {{node}}, {{npm}}, and {{npx}} commands will use it.

h3. Per-Project Version Pinning

To pin a specific Node.js version for a project, run the following from within the project directory:

{code:language=bash}
volta pin node@lts
{code}

This adds a {{volta}} field to your {{package.json}}, and Volta will automatically use the pinned version whenever you work in that directory.

h3. Verify

{code:language=bash}
volta --version
node --version
npm --version
{code}

